The paper deals with the problem of recommending sections for Wikipedia articles, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses topic modeling and collaborative filtering, which are common techniques in natural language processing and machine learning, suggesting cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.DL (Digital Libraries) as likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses evaluation metrics such as precision@10, which are commonly used in machine learning and data mining, indicating cs.LG (Machine Learning) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with recommendation systems, which are a common application of artificial intelligence, suggesting cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible sub-category.
